On Mon, 17 Jan 2000, Alan Cox wrote:
> Hundreds of people will be glad to provide orbs with two hop test relays.
> In fact if someone was to get that stupid then orbs has a database of
> hundreds of thousands of open mail relays for two hop testing.
> 
> Alan
If I deny access to someone and someone else purposely allows themself to
be used as a gateway to my resources to a denied host, they risk being cut
off themselves.
The bottom line is that there IS a responsible open relay filter out
there, the MAPS RSS (Relay Spam Stopper) that I myself use and I encourage
others to use. Relay spam is a bad thing and should be stopped.
